title: What's happened to Rita Ora's face? Singer looks VERY different as she attends Fifty Shades Darker premiere
text:
What's happened to Rita Ora's face? Singer looks VERY different as she attends Fifty Shades Darker premiere The former X Factor judge didn't look her usual self as she hit the red carpet Share Comments By Vicki Newman 22:34, 9 FEB 2017 Celebs Katie Price gets glammed up for the Fifty Shades Pregnant Amal and George Clooney jets into LAX da 0:27 Kerry Katona rejoins the Kittens on stage after m 1:01 Kim Kardashian shares her VERY FIRST magazine app 0:33 Celebs hit the red carpet at amfAR's New York gala 0:48 Tom Jones spotted with Priscilla Presley in Holly 1:14 THAT famous Tara Palmer-Tomkinson interview with 0:39 Remembering Tara Palmer-Tomkinson's fiery appeara 1:29 Tara Palmer-Tomkinson - key moments from the life 2:49 Massive power cut plunges Brussels into darkness 0:38 Sprinter James Ellington already back in training 0:24 Audio-free: Read through of the obscure laws that 0:52 Jack Branning furious as real cause of Ronnie and 0:59 England rugby press conference with Eddie Jones a 10:15 Video will play in A ring on engagement finger and a new look for Rita Ora! celebs Rita Ora showcased a VERY different look as she walked the red carpet at the Fifty Shades Darker premiere.
The former X Factor judge was almost difficult to recognise when she first stepped out at the star-studded event in London's Leicester Square on Thursday night.
The RIP hitmaker had a very taut appearance and facially, looked very different to the fresh-faced pop star we all know.
Rita took to Snapchat earlier in the night to share a selfie alongside the caption: "New look new me".
Read More Katie Price snogs husband Kieran Hayler on the red carpet as they attend Fifty Shades Darker premiere Rita looked very different at the premiere (Photo: PA) She's pictured here in New York City just a few months ago (Photo: Nancy Rivera/Splash News) New look, new me? (Photo: Rita Ora/snapchat) Rita, who mentored Louisa Johnson to victory on the ITV talent show in 2015, seems to have changed a lot in the last couple of years.
She put on quite the display at the premiere in a show-stopping gown.
The navy halterneck ensemble complimented off her figure beautifully, showing off just a hint of underboob to give it some edge.
Her high ponytail pulled her hair away from her face and accentuated her high cheek bones.
But she looks very different to her X Factor days just two years ago.
Read More Protester crashes Fifty Shades Darker premiere with banner saying the films 'groom women for abuse' Rita used to be a judge on the X Factor (Photo: Splash) She mentored Louisa Johnson to victory in 2005 (Photo: Splash) Rita has reprised her role in the film franchise as Mia, the sister of main character, billionaire businessman Christian Grey.
She was ridiculed by fans the first time around for only having three lines make it to the final cut of Fifty Shades Of Grey.
Rita may also spark speculation that she's engaged after sharing an image of herself wearing a huge diamond ring on her wedding finger.
She posted it to Snapchat with the caption: "Thank you Tiffany's".
Is Rita engaged? (Photo: Rita Ora/snapchat) Rita celebrates with Louisa (Photo: Splash) The films, which star Dakota Johnson and Jamie Dornan , are based on a series of erotic novels by EL James.
They follow Anastasia Steele as she embarks on a sexual relationship with the wealthy Christian Grey only to discover that he has some dark desires and the need to control everything.
James was shocked by the explosion of interest in her books, originally released in 2011.
She described the trilogy as her 'mid-life crisis on paper' and said they included "all her fantasies".
Mirror Celeb has contacted Rita's representatives for comment.
